Relaxed atmosphere

reviews.title: Culinary surprises
reviews.text: Recently with Business Circle Urk had a fantastic evening here. A beautiful terrace with beautiful views of the Urk harbour. But if this was not enough, the most delicious dishes with surprising combinations came along. I thought every time the dish after this must be disappointing because it doesn't get better than this. Luckily Cees the Chef managed to amaze me every time. Highly recommended for everyone!!!

reviews.title: Summer at De Boet
reviews.text: On a warm summer day on the shaded terrace enjoying the delicious fish salad ‘de Boet’... that is really summer. The slow-cooked pork belly was delicious!

tips.body: Goede wijnkaart! Vraag advies…veel kennis aanwezig.

reviews.title: Definitely recommended
reviews.text:
On a warm afternoon in late July on the beautiful terrace enjoyed an exquisite lunch of 3 courses.
All 3 courses were exquisite. Price quality a 10 out of 10.
There is also a very extensive wine list at very acceptable prices.
Only downside was that the owner may not serve wine glasses on the terrace so one must drink the wine from a water glass.
I find this very strange. (Maybe consider providing less expensive glasses for the terrace in the future?)
The rest was great. Thanks for a lovely afternoon.

reviews.title: Excellent!
reviews.text:
Night out together, delicious food, as we are used to from the Boet.

Kind regards, Hendrik and Mariska

reviews.title: "Culinary Evening of Enjoyment at Restaurant 'De Boet' on Urk"
reviews.text: A night out with friends. Then we'll go to De Boet. It is always enjoyable at restaurant 'De Boet' on Urk. A wonderful evening with various dishes; the combinations of flavors and textures are a feast. Supplemented with a 'butter' wine Don Doriac, our evening can not go wrong. We will definitely be back. Compliments to the service, everything checks out!

reviews.title: A taste experience full of surprises, highly recommended!
reviews.text:
Had dinner at a wedding. We all got fantastic dishes during a tasting menu. Highly recommended if you want to go for a taste experience full of surprises!  
With a nice atmosphere and luxurious experience with good service. And all in the beautiful location with the view of the port of Urk. I will definitely recommend a visit to restaurant de Boet;)

tips.body: Als je voor een smaakbeleving vol verrassingen wil gaan is het proeverij menu zeker een aanrader!

reviews.title: Excellent food experience
reviews.text: Great place with great views and delicious exceptional flavor palette of flavors in the dishes. Meanwhile, you can enjoy the setting sun in the IJsselmeer

reviews.title: Fantastic
reviews.text:
Educational but above all fun and nice cooking workshop with the family. If you are looking for a nice getaway with family, colleagues or friends, this is ideal. Cook together and then have dinner. 
I will definitely be back! 
Cees thank you! 🥂

reviews.title: Cooking workshop is highly recommended!
reviews.text: We had booked a cooking workshop at Cees van De Boet on the recommendation of a friend. We were 7 very different adults and we all really liked it. It was fun with Cees: he is very animated and passionate about cooking and eating, and we learned a lot from him. Furthermore, the 3-course lunch (partly) prepared by us was also very tasty and tasteful. In short, highly recommended! Moreover, there are different types of cooking workshops to book at De Boet, so we will definitely go again.

reviews.title: Indulgence
reviews.text: Delicious food. From amuse, starter, main course and the delicious dessert. Friendly service who are knowledgeable. Recommended

reviews.title: Rejected
reviews.text:
Dinner with high expectations, given that we ate really well during a week in Holland. Complete disappointment: unclear menu, I find this proposal of courses not comfortable and not compliant with our culture. All the dishes chosen did not have enough momentum to review this restaurant in the Michelin Guide.
Luckily I have some experience with high-level restaurants and I absolutely do not recommend this one. It's a shame because I threw away a token to try other restaurants that had been recommended to me. The only positive note was the girl who served us, polite, polite and professional.

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

articleContent.title: Meet the Ascend Collection resorts travelers are buzzing about

seoInfo.metaDescription: If a resort getaway is on your list this year, look no further. Earning top ratings, Ascend Collection resorts stand out with premium amenities and memorable cultural experiences. Discover what you’ll love about these one-of-a-kind resorts and unmissable destinations in this roundup inspired by real traveler reviews.

articleContent.title: How many days in Cape Town is enough?

seoInfo.metaDescription: Here’s how you make the most of the South African city, no matter how short or long your stay.

When you’re headed to Barcelona—especially if it’s your first time—five days is probably the sweet spot. There’s plenty of time to fit in all the must-sees, like the jaw-dropping Sagrada Familia. You can ramble down the Ramblas, pause in front of Art-Nouveau mansions on the Passeig de Gracia, and gasp at the views of the city skyline from the hillside Parc de Montjuïc. Feel like taking an extra-long lunch to enjoy tapas (or their Basque cousins, pintxos)? Go ahead. I promise you that you won’t feel rushed.

articleContent.title: Inside Athens’ burgeoning street art scene

seoInfo.metaDescription: There's creativity at every turn in the Greek capital

There’s no other way to put this: Marrakech is a lot. But is it too much to take in when you only have a pair of days to explore? My first trip here lasted just two days, and after spending a few hours in the Medina—the crowded, chaotic market where leather tanners, carpet makers, spice sellers, and others set up shop—I still had plenty of time to take in the rest of the city. The trick is to take lots of breaks, stopping to enjoy a bag of figs in one of the pretty parks or a tagine at one of the open-air eateries. And bonus: The people watching here is next level.

tripContent.title: Celebrate Nevada's history, rhythm, and culture
tripContent.description: Nevada’s story is etched in historic mining towns, roadside wonders, galleries, and museums. From frontier heritage and atomic relics to glowing neon art, every stop reveals a new layer of the state's past and present. Whether you're wandering small-town streets or stepping into iconic city museums, this journey blends memory and motion in a way that’s anything but ordinary.

reviews.title: Eaten well
reviews.text: Eaten well! You can go here for individual dishes or a menu that you put together yourself. The dishes are tasty, the fish fresh. The recommended wine/food combination is good. A friendly hostess, the other staff not in the best of moods (combination of age/insecurity?). Definitely worth a visit.

reviews.title: Delicious and good-looking food
reviews.text: I like my food to look and taste good, and De Boet is giving you exactly that. The menu is vegetarian-friendly (not just the boring veggie-risotto option you normally see) making it a recommendable place for everyone!

mgmtResponse.text: Thank you very much for these positive kind words

reviews.title: Excellent value for money
reviews.text: We had lunch and were pleasantly surprised. Good atmosphere, good service and excellent food. Service was not too slow nor too fast.

reviews.title: Unexpected
reviews.text:
The Dutch like to travel by boat during holidays.no wonder, with so much water around.so, one moves from one interesting spot to the other and one in three days one tends to eat outside the ships kitchen (pantry or kombuis). In most cases one is happy with decent tourist food. So it came as a complete surprise to encouter really well designed and well coocked dishes in a place called Urk! Which is not intended to deminish the charme of Urk in the slightest! Urk is fascinating enough, but for reasons of its history as a past island in the sea that the Dutch turned into land. It is not known for its cuisine, other than processing large quantities of fish.
This restaurant serves fish as well  and we had small portions of canadian lobster with schol and devil fish, but the quality of processing, taste, serving,  hospitaliry etc, went levels above what we expected.even the cheese desert was outstanding.
So after months of silence: if you are in Urk, with or without a boat, be there!!!

mgmtResponse.text: Thank you for this very positive reaction about Urk and our restaurant.

reviews.title: top food - poor service - what a pity
reviews.text:
to start with the positive things: the kitchen is really good!!! 
however, the service we experienced was very poor, not only for a top restaurant but even by the standards of a tourist town - and the place was not overly busy
a few examples:
- some drinks were forgotten, and even after that was recognized it took more than 10 min to correct for it
- more than 30 min and asking twice before we could see the menue 
- after asking twice I finally got up to get the wine list myself
- the wine arrived after the first courses were finished 
I ll stop here, but it went on like that
we finally asked the bill and gave them the (payed for) desert as a gift ...
In conclusion: excellent cuisine in combination with a poor service is probably not worth the money and kills a possible great experience 
hopefully the person taking care of us was a poor example? but the 14 year old who was helping her and was really doing his best also for me is a hint that management does not take service seriously...

I

reviews.title: Small conference dinner
reviews.text:
The restaurant has a lovely atmosphere, the service was great and the food was super delicious!!
We were a group of 20-25 people from various countries, all enjoyed very much this evening!

reviews.title: Beautiful Cosy Delicious
reviews.text:
A very beautiful cosy restaurant at the harbour of Urk with a few on all the boats, but not too overwhelming as the windows are tiny. 

The food is delicious, tiny dishes, looks excellent, very well thought of -compliments to the chef- and the service is very friendly. It is somewhat expensive but totally worth it.

reviews.title: Great (sea) food - service could be slightly improved
reviews.text: Really nice atmosphere at this restaurant in Urk. Food was really good with lot's of nice small side dishes served on the house. Service could slightly be improved to match the same level as the excellent food.

reviews.title: Flavours! Wow!
reviews.text: We were in Urk for one night only and booked this restaurant after reading its reviews on here! We weren’t disappointed. We opted for the 4 course menu which was superb. Shame that it’s a bit far for us to come back!

reviews.title: Fantastic food
reviews.text:
We had dinner in this restaurant,  we choose for the 4 course menu. It was a good choice, we opted for fish, greatly prepared. 
First sole with lobster then local eels and then plaice with mashed potatoes and parsley.
They have a good wine list, affordable priced.
Service was good
In summertime reservation should be recommended, you can do this online 
Overall very good and we would certainly recommend it
Price: around 175 euro for 4 courses, wine & water

reviews.title: Good soup
reviews.text: Very nice location in the Middle of Harbour. We had sea food soup only. It was good and tasty. Freshly cooked.

reviews.title: For the fishlovers
reviews.text: Perfect dutch fish plate is what you can fins here. We went with our dutch friend who knew this place and he was absolutely right. I have never heard about Urk before but if have the chance i will come back again

reviews.title: BEAUTIFUL FOOD - EXCELLENT WINE SELECTION
reviews.text: Urk is an old fishing port, now greatly modernised but with a fine harbour and an excellent range of very good restaurants. De Boet is almost certainly the finest. In an excellent harbour-side position with beautiful, elegant food and a great range of wines which can be purchased by the glass. The menu is designed around the catch of the day, so is not extensive. But the food is fresh and artistically presented. Portions are modest but a 3 course lunch menu was just enough. Such fine food and meticulous attention to detail will not come cheap so expect to spend upwards of fifty euros per person.

reviews.title: Definitely worth a visit
reviews.text: The former Island of Urk is worth a visit for it's picturesque and somewhat different from the rest of the Netherlands. De Boet though in itself is worth a detour, even if you don't have time for the rest of the island. Nice and surprising combinations of ingredients and flavor, delicate but tasteful and friendly service at a very decent price. Highly recommended.

reviews.title: Fantastic food,wine & highly skilled servicelevel
reviews.text: I visited this restaurant while on a business trip during two consecutive nights in the 3rd week of march. Very convenient as we stayed at  B&B de Roos ( which I also can recommend) next door. We enjoyed both the fish and meat menu and were impressed by the quality and presentation of the ( fresh) food as well as the excellent service. Our waitress/hostess was not only very charming but also highly skilled .You eat and drink well at this place for about Euro 100,- ; in my hometown Oslo this would be at least double the price. Thank you all staffmembers for making our visit so pleasant and we will certainly be back on our next business stay in Flevoland.

reviews.title: excellent
reviews.text: A beautiful restaurant, very clean and modern. Food was to die for, very tasty and well presented. Staff very polite and friendly

reviews.title: Last Friday we had a very delicious dinner in restaurant DE Boet at Urk.
reviews.text:
An excellent 3-course dinner during which we had a choice between fish and meat.
The service was very good and professional.

reviews.title: Absolutely fabulous! Top restaurant!
reviews.text:
We visited Urk for a day with the family and had lunch at this fine restaurant. The three-course meal was exceptional and definitely one of the best I've ever had. It was creative, looked great and tasted amazing. The portions were just right for someone like myself who generally is not a huge eater. The tiny amuses were mouth-watering.
Lovely setting near the water, knowledgeable and accommodating staff.

reviews.title: Fantastic food in a friendly ambiance
reviews.text: The food was elegantly composed, the flavours were surprising and the wine complemented the food superbly, bringing out the beat in the food and the wine. This all in a no nonsense environment created an impression to be remembered.

reviews.title: Fine dinning by the water
reviews.text:
My friend and chef that i work with brought me here for a super meal. This restaurant has a great reputation with the chefs that work in nearby Lelystad.
We enjoyed many courses and glasses of wine. 
I cannot remember what we ate exactly but I do remember perfectly cooked monkfish or devilfish as I think the Dutch call it. A couple different small plates featuring white and green asparagus as it was the season for them. We had a wonderful cheese selection also.
All plates were put together beutifully. As I am a chef I appreciate seeing the care that goes into knife work, food quality and plating. Its not just about cooking.
I was a nice treat to have a few beers at one of the cozy pubs down the way from here. Walk around the cobblestone streets to check out the shops, wooden boats in the harbor and then finish it off with this top notch restaurant.

reviews.title: What a nice place
reviews.text:
We were so lucky tone here on a warm June evening and chooses to dine outside
Relaxing view of the marina
I love the place
Food was excellent and the monkfish with risotto and asparagus was amazing
Lovely dessert and fresh bread
Wine choice also very good
Thumbs up, eat here for business, family, friends or for a romantic eve. You will love it

reviews.title: Nice discovery..
reviews.text: The very nicely transformed barn offers a comfortable seating for the curious guest looking for a gastronomic evening...We were impressed by the good reception, the nice and friendly young waiters and waitresses and by the delicious very fresh fish dishes... A definite must whenever you plan to visit Urk for whatever reason. Fine Dutch dining with a original reasonable diverse wine-list.

reviews.title: Great tastes, great quality
reviews.text:
Allthough I expected something else from the best restaurant of Flevoland (Lekker 500 2016), I really was amazed by the tastes of the food. What I expected was a small miracle on my plate regarding tastes, forms and textures, but what I got was just great prepared food. Especially the pumpkinsoup. This was 'just' pumpkinsoup in a (nice) bowl, but the combination with the fish and the taste of the soup itself were marvellous.
Next to that, try to get a windowseat and I'm sure you'll love the view.
Finally, the service was silent, nice and knowledgable.

reviews.title: When in Urk eat here!
reviews.text: Although the lack of competition made this restaurant a logic place for my friends and me to go to, it is a great place for good food. When in Urk you must eat fish so that is what we did. Drinking a nice glass of white wine with it. We were lucky to be able to sit on the outside terras. Enjoying the sun go down. The food is af great standard. Fresh products and presented in a stylish way.

reviews.title: Outstanding dinner - quality throughout
reviews.text: Don't offer an excellent rating often but De Boet surprised and exceeded expectations by a long margin. This is a relatively new (4 y/o) establishment in a tastefully renovated building on the harbor. Previously have dined at other restaurants in Urk but with ordinary or lesser satisfaction. This place has class way beyond this seaside/rural location and kitchen and service capability to match. Enthusiasm and imagination was evident in every dish. Three different amuse bouches of style arrived while five of us ordered. It's a small but interesting set menu of three courses if you want and options to opt up to some specialities. Between courses came further little tastes. Space prevents descriptions of each dish as they were all complex combinations of ingredients, flavor, texture and color. A quiet night so enjoyed fine service and enjoyed quality wines from a good list. Must return when next in Netherlands - pray it continues like this.

reviews.title: Probably the best food in Urk
reviews.text: Prices are a bit steep, but if you want a very good lunch or diner, stop at de boet. The menu is short, but carefully chosen.

reviews.title: Restaurant overlooking the harbour of Urk
reviews.text: We were Lucky with the weather and sat on the terrace. The food was good, and the prices reasonable. Wines also.

reviews.title: Excellent Seafood away from Amsterdam
reviews.text: I had lunch there with a friend and we had the 3 course set menu lunch. Each course was not only fresh and flavorful it was also carefully plated. This is an excellent restaurant located on the sea front in Urk.

reviews.title: Tasteful dinner for reasonable price
reviews.text:
This was the third time we tried this restaurant (once as Les Amis and now for the second time as De Boet). Also this time we enjoyed our evening very much.
The restaurant is located in a renovated building on the harbour. Our table at the window had great views of the fishing boats. The interior of the restaurant is very stylish and minimalist with nice local details. It is impressive to see how well organised the chefs are working in the open kitchen.
Our waitress was very kind, smiling, helpful and professional. Service was quick.
We had a 4-course dinner with several amuses-bouche for 36 euros. All dishes were lovely presented, very well prepared and tasteful. Any wine on the menu could be ordered by the  glass, so one has easily the possibility to try different wines.
We think that this restaurant offers a very good quality for a very reasonable price. 
The only minor detail was that it was a bit cold at our table at the window, but thus said, it was a very cold, windy and rainy evening.
We will surely come back in De Boet in future.

reviews.title: Orignal regional fish place
reviews.text: The food was very orginal and beautifully presented.  Loved the makrel tatare. Delicious amuses-bouche in between. The cod was fresh and delicious but coukd have done without the buttery sauce. Deserts looked boring so went for cheese. These were not special or regional enough we thought.  Service was friendly and prompt.  10 points for the typical Urk style details in tge decoration. Very nice touch.  Great initiative in a little village like this. Worth the trip !

reviews.title: Hospitality and creative cuisine
reviews.text: We enjoyed having diner with friends. Good timing of service and creative dishes with a great taste. Accompanying wines were very nice.

reviews.title: Excelent food, nice company
reviews.text: Right on the harbor site of Urk an excellent fish restaurant. The fish they serve comes right from the sea. Visit Urk and enjoy a lovely diner in the Boet.

reviews.title: Superb!
reviews.text:
I had my birthday dinner here together with my family. It was superb!

De Boet is quite new. They are situated in the centre of Urk with a view over the harbour. The chef and hostess used to own/work in Mes Amies, next door.
They renovated/rebuild an old warehouse and harbor office into a very tasteful, modern but warm restaurant. In spring/summer they also have a terrace outside.

The menu is seasonal and changes regularly. From it you can choose a 3, 4 or 5 course meal. EUR 37,50 for 3, 47,50 for 4 and 52,50 for 5 courses. The wine options are also very good.
Quite some fish choices on the menu, but also very nice meat options.
The combinations are not standard and exquisite. Everything is fresh.

Next to our 4 course meal we got a lot of very tasteful amuses, even just before desert.

The service was very professional and friendly, but not too. 

We'll be back!
